content:
 I wanted to try something new (and, naturally, I&rsquo;m running out of content ideas), so let me introduce the hashtag #gtmtips. I hope others contribute as well, but I will be adding a new tip as often as possible. I&rsquo;ve got maybe 20 tips in store right now, and I&rsquo;m writing new ones all the time. So without further ado, here&rsquo;s&hellip;
Tip 1: Save GATC In A Constant String Macro   This is an easy one, and everyone should already be doing this in one way or another. The point is that you shouldn&rsquo;t use strings in fields which are often used. Save the string in a macro, so all you have to do is refer to the macro in all your tags. That way, if the string ever changes (for example, when transferring to another property), you don&rsquo;t have to rewrite the field in all your tags.
Dead simple!
